news.title: Gujarat cabinet approves formation of nine new municipal corporations
news.para: The new municipal corporations are coming into existence after 14 years. The Gandhinagar Municipal Corporation was the last one to be formed by the government in 2010.

news.title: Indore and Ujjain sees surge in property registrations in 2024
news.para: Indore and Ujjain emerged as the top performers, primarily driven by the ongoing developmental activities in the region.

news.title: Gurugram civic body's chief orders action against official for delaying property ID correction file
news.para: The commissioner has proposed a chargesheet under rule 7 (major penalty) of the Haryana civil services (punishment and appeal) rules, 2016.

news.title: Kanpur: Official suspended for allocating PMAY housing to 15 ineligible beneficiaries
news.para: Approximately 30 days ago, chief development officer (CDO) Deeksha Jain received a complaint from Madhai Nivada village resident Jitendra Singh, stating that village development officer Manoj Verma distributed housing funds to roughly 28 unqualified recipients in Shivrajpur block during the past year.

news.title: Nagpur civic body launches amnesty scheme to recover Rs 850 crore in property tax arrears
news.para: The scheme offers 80% waiver on penalties and interest, reducing the outstanding property tax amount of Rs 850.1 crore, along with Rs 770.45 crore in fine and interest, under the Property Tax Amnesty Scheme 2024-2025.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: CRDA starts tender process for Amaravati
news.para: CRDA is aiming to complete the tender process by Jan-end so that works can be launched by Feb 1. The works proposed in phase I are estimated to cost about Rs 2,300 crore.

news.title: Pune civic body to snap water connections of property tax defaulters
news.para: "The civic administration has formed five flying squads to survey the defaulters, who will be subjected to action. Both commercial and residential properties will be under scrutiny," said Madhav Jagtap, head of PMC's property tax department.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Police find 192 hotels operating without proper documentation
news.para: A team led by DCP City Rajesh Kumar inspected 122 hotels and lodges on Tuesday and sealed 56 that were not in compliance with regulations. In the rural areas, police teams led inspected 108 hotels, sealing 54 hotels and lodges that lacked proper registration.

news.title: Guntur civic body may levy penalty on owners of unkempt plots
news.para: The civic body has identified about 20,000 vacant and unkempt sites in the city which have become mosquito breeding centres due to improper maintenance.

news.title: Maharashtra to draft affordable homes plan in 100 days
news.para: The RDD has proposed to set up land and sand banks to avoid shortage. Efforts will be made for speedy approval of loan proposals.

news.title: India Cements appoints Suresh Patil as CEO following promoter's exit
news.para: The board of India Cements Ltd (ICL) has approved the appointment of Suresh Vasant Patil as CEO and Krishnagopal Ladsaria as CFO, the company said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Rural development ministry aims to sanction 10 lakh PMAY-G houses in January 2025
news.para: An official statement said the ministry will set monthly goals to ensure the implementation of rural development schemes on time and to help realise Prime Minister Narendra Modi's dream of creating a poverty-free India.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body proposes new rules for leasing its properties
news.para: Anticipating a windfall either by selling or leasing the properties through public auction process, the civic body has proposed to link its properties' rent with their guidance value along with a fixed term of lease.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to sell Manimajra land for new housing project
news.para: The project spans 6.8 acres (4,840 sq yd) and will include flats constructed in five designated pockets.

news.title: Mumbai: R-Central ward halts work at 66 construction sites in Borivali & Byculla
news.para: TMC issued show-cause notices to 39 construction sites for allegedly flouting dust pollution control mandates. Panvel City Municipal Corporation, too, served notices to 164 builders for violating pollution norms.

news.title: Noida: Maintenance agency reinstates services in Jaypee Greens Kosmos
news.para: The AOA, however, expressed its inability to manage these services as the company did not transfer the bank accounts or the balance amount collected as charges paid so far by the residents towards such services.

news.title: Metro Brands promoters buy three apartments for Rs 243 crore in Mumbai’s Worli
news.para: The latest three apartments acquired by the family are spread over more than 23,000 sq ft in total and are located on the 61st and 62nd floor of India’s tallest and one of the most expensive residential towers Palais Royale.

news.title: Australian home prices finally cool as 2024 comes to an end
news.para: Figures from property consultant CoreLogic, released on Thursday, showed prices across the nation dipped 0.1% in December from the prior month, while values in the major capitals fell 0.2%.

news.title: Chandigarh metro project once again come to screeching halt
news.para: However, by the end of the year, this outlook changed dramatically as questions were raised about the project's financial viability.
